\f0\fs24 \cf0 README FILE\
---------------\
Title: Crisis-Time Enfranchisement and the Persistence of Protest Behaviour\
Authors: Bernard Sarpong and Jun Goto\
Date: November 2025\
Software: Stata 18\
\
OVERVIEW\
-----------------\
This dataset and accompanying Stata do-file support the paper "Crisis-Time Enfranchisement and the Persistence of Protest Behaviour."\
The analysis examines whether cohorts enfranchised during macroeconomic crises are more likely to engage in protests later in life,\
using harmonised data from the World Values Survey and European Values Survey (1981\'962022) merged with macroeconomic crisis episodes\
identified from Barro and Urs\'faa (2008) and the Maddison Project Database (2024). The do-file includes procedures for data preparation,\
treatment construction, estimation, robustness checks, and figure generation. The empirical strategy employs OLS models with country,\
cohort, and survey-year fixed effects, clustering standard errors at the cohort-country level. Required Stata packages include reghdfe,\
estout, and coefplot. All data sources are publicly available, and users must obtain them directly from the original providers. The\
code ensures reproducibility of all results presented in the paper\'92s tables and figures.\
\
Purpose of the Code\
-------------------\
The Stata do-file (\'93Protest_do_file.do\'94) implements all empirical procedures used in the study, including data\
preparation, merging, treatment assignment, estimation, and generation of summary statistics and figures.\
\
